<zyQSetTF caption="Constant variables." id="ac4bb763-7075-6aab-8588-d776c9cf4327">
Which of the following statements are valid declarations <!--and-->or uses of a constant integer variable named STEP_SIZE? Assume that variables totalStepHeight and numSteps have previously been declared as integers.

<zyQ>
<zyQText correct="False"><zyICode>int STEP_SIZE = 5;</zyICode></zyQText>
<zyQExpl>Declares and initializes an int variable, but the variable is not a constant.  </zyQExpl>
</zyQ>

<zyQ>
<zyQText correct="True"><zyICode>final int STEP_SIZE = 14;</zyICode></zyQText>
<zyQExpl>Declares a constant int variable STEP_SIZE and initializes the constant with the value 14.  </zyQExpl>
</zyQ>

<zyQ>
<zyQText correct="True"><zyICode>totalStepHeight = numSteps * STEP_SIZE;</zyICode></zyQText>
<zyQExpl>Constant variables can be used in expressions just like other variables.  </zyQExpl>
</zyQ>

<zyQ>
<zyQText correct="False"><zyICode>STEP_SIZE = STEP_SIZE + 1;</zyICode></zyQText>
<zyQExpl>Results in a compilation error. Constant variables cannot be changed within assignment statements.   </zyQExpl>
</zyQ>
</zyQSetTF>
